## Testing workflow

### STEP 1: Start servers

```bash
# Backend (from MonitoringAi/DashboardApi)
cd MonitoringAi/DashboardApi && dotnet run &

# Frontend (from MonitoringAi/DashboardFrontend)
cd MonitoringAi/DashboardFrontend && npm run dev &

# Wait for startup (e.g. 5 seconds)
sleep 5
```

(Note: Backend NUnit tests live in `MonitoringAi/Tests` — run `dotnet test` from there, not from DashboardApi.)

### STEP 2: Quick smoke test

- Open **http://localhost:5173** (or the port Vite prints, e.g. 5174/5175)
- Open DevTools (F12) → Console: **no red errors**
- Confirm dark theme loads
- Click through: Dashboard, Chat, Admin, Q&A, Watchlist (if present)

### STEP 3: Core functionality

| Area | Checks |
|------|--------|
| **Dashboard** | Invalid name "test" → error; valid "Test Dashboard" → accepts; uncheck default → dropdown; no crashes |
| **Chat** | Settings modal opens; can enter API key; can type/send (send works if key valid) |
| **Admin** | Add query (e.g. Category: Account, Key: "test query", Value: "SELECT..."); appears in table; edit/delete; changes persist after reload |
| **Common Q&A** | Search filters results; Copy works (paste to verify); categories expand/collapse |
| **Watchlist** | 17 tickers in correct order; can add/remove tickers (if UI exists) |
| **Market News** | Only SPY, QQQ, TSLA, NVDA, AMZN; max 15 articles (if feature exists) |

### STEP 4: Backend tests

```bash
cd MonitoringAi/Tests
dotnet test
```

Require **100% pass**.

### STEP 5: Security check

- Console: no CSP errors, no CORS errors
- No XSS (coordinate with @Paul if needed)

